column5: This video was taken back in June of this year.  For those that don't know, this is my second hobby.  I'm the guy with the red guitar.  Hope you enjoy!  <object width="340" height="240"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KN1-6bUchuA&hl=en&fs=1"></param><param'>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KN1-6bUchuA&hl=en&fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KN1-6bUchuA&hl=en&fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="340" height="240"></embed></object>
That's kewl - thanks for sharing!
Nice! That looks like an Ibanez Roadstar. I had one when I was in my early teens!
Good eye...yep...that's an Ibanez Roadstar II....bought brand new in about 1986.
what happen to the OFC  theme song........thought for sure that wouldve been included in the set...........lol    thxs for sharing.....you guys sound good   cheers pete
Very good. Good lead guitar!
I work night shift and sleep during the day, I don't need that kind of racket while I'm trying to sleep!!!  I demand that you cease and desist immediately or I'm calling the Cops!!!
LOL....too bad for you then....  That's what earplugs are for.
Very nice Cliff.  You guys seem to be getting better and better everytime I hear you  Tuned in for sure  Plus I like your choice of songs.  Joey
dude, where's the RAMONES!
LOL...we played two Ramones tunes that day, unfortunately, we didn't record the whole gig.  No one had them on tape or they would have been included.
Cool video and great songs Cliff    Your a natural on front stage  Thanks for sharing Leechman

that's pretty cool man, me and some of my long time jammin buddy's are just about to start setting up a few local gigs....we try to get together at least once a week if possible although sometimes hard in the summer time because of work, and well ummm fishin..but we have about 100 songs down pretty good now so I think we can play some gigs no prob..  The only thing that sucks about being the entertainment at a party though is while you are rockin out, everyone else is having a good time and drinking all the beer
Great job Cliff, thanks for sharing.
pretty solid  cut some high end out of that bass and u are gold
Thanks Cliff I enjoyed that very much.  Is that the house I almost visited  MTP

Thanks everyone!  MTP - Nope...not my house...LOL.  Micropterus - I hear you on the bass.  That's what happens when there are no monitors or mixing going on.  We didn't get a real sound check outside, so that's our own fault on the sound.  jwl - Very cool!  100 songs?  Wow...that's a lot of material.  Our guys just keep their beer on their amplifiers....hehe.

Cripes !...I agree with the Dawg...  I hope I don't have to listen to that down on Big Cliff's Dock on Saturday...  The noise will scare all the carp away !!!  Just kidding Cliff...nice job on the tunes...
Nice vid cliff.
Awesome GIG man, i need to pick up the guitar and drums again... there getting dusty!!!  I smell lessons? LOL
